<TITLE> Obama tells Putin relations with Russia can improve </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NOVO OGARYOVO, Russia, Jul 7 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - President Barack Obama told Prime Minister Vladimir Putin on Tuesday that they may not agree on everything but that they had an excellent opportunity to put relations on a much stronger footing. Putin, at the start of a breakfast meeting with Obama, said Russia was linking hopes for better relations with the United States with Obama. The US leader said Putin had done extraordinary work as president and prime minister
